title: Stocks to watch at noon on Monday
text:
Mon, Jul 13, 2015, 3:48 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 12 mins. Stocks to watch at noon on Monday AAP – 3 hours ago 
Stocks to watch on the Australian stock exchange at noon on Monday: 
ANZ - ANZ BANKING GROUP - down 18 cents, or 0.6 per cent, at $32.07 
CBA - COMMONWEALTH BANK - down one cent, or 0.01 per cent, at $85.78 
NAB - NATIONAL AUSTRALIA BANK - down 11 cents, or 0.3 per cent, at $32.94 
WBC - WESTPAC BANKING CORPORATION - up 1.5 cents, or 0.05 per cent, at $33.115 
The big four banks would need to lift their capital reserve levels by about one sixth in order to meet a key recommendation of the Financial Systems Inquiry. 
MAH - MACMAHON HOLDINGS - steady at seven cents 
Troubled mining services company Macmahon Holdings has promoted chief financial officer Sybrandt van Dyk to chief executive. 
VAH - VIRGIN AUSTRALIA - down 0.25 cents, or 0.6 per cent, at 43.25 cents 
QAN - QANTAS AIRWAYS - up 11 cents, or 3.3 per cent, at $3.44 
Virgin Australia has cancelled all flights into and out of Bali on Monday due to the threat posed by a volcanic ash cloud. 
WCB - WARRNAMBOOL CHEESE AND BUTTER FACTORY - steady at $9.60 
Dairy producer Warrnambool Cheese and Butter Factory still expects dairy prices to remain weak, with no improvement until late 2015 at the earliest. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Aldi defends its tax record AAP 
Discount supermarket chain Aldi has defended its tax record amid a more than doubling in profit over four years. …
